In 1963, a young radical teacher named Jerry Rubin co-founded the first alternative high school in the United States, located in the Bronx. The radical ideas that Rubin brought with him to the classroom were ahead of their time, and he quickly became a controversial figure in the world of education. This piece explores the story of Rubin and the creation of his radical school, and examines the impact that his ideas had on the education system and on the wider culture of the time.

AI and the Future of Work: An Interview with Dr. Andrew Ng
Dr. Andrew Ng, the founder of Landing AI and a former Chief Scientist at Baidu, has been a leading voice in the field of artificial intelligence (AI) for many years. In this interview, he talks about the potential impact of AI on the future of work and what we can do to prepare for it.
Dr. Andrew Ng: What I see happening is that AI is going to automate many tasks that currently require human labor. This is going to lead to a significant shift in the job market. Some jobs are going to be replaced entirely, while others are going to change dramatically.
The key to preparing for this shift is to focus on developing skills that are hard for computers to replicate, such as creativity, empathy, and complex problem-solving. These are the skills that will be in high demand in the future.
At the same time, we need to be proactive in retraining workers who are at risk of losing their jobs. This is why initiatives like Universal Basic Skills are so important. They provide people with the foundational skills they need to succeed in the future job market.
